Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Drain @pineapple{4%oz}. (TIP: Save the pineapple juice for adding to smoothies or cocktails!) Quarter @grape tomatoes{4%oz}. Pick @cilantro{1/4%oz} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves and stems, keeping them separate. Halve, peel, and finely chop @shallot{1}. Finely chop @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Drain and rinse @black beans{13.4%oz}.

== Cilantro Lime Rice ==

In a small #pot, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Smoky Red Pepper Crema ==

While rice cooks, in a small #bowl, combine @smoky red pepper crema{4%tbsp} with a squeeze of lime juice. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt and @pepper.

== Pineapple Salsa ==

In a separate small #bowl, combine pineapple, tomatoes, half the cilantro leaves, half the shallot, juice from remaining lime, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with @salt and @pepper.

== Black Bean Patties ==

Transfer beans to a medium #bowl; mash with a #potato masher{} or fork until almost smooth. (It's OK if there are still some larger pieces.)

Add @tempura mix{82%g}, @southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{3/4%tsp}, and 1/3 cup water (1 1/2 tsp salt and 2/3 cup water for 4 servings); stir until thoroughly combined. TIP: Batter should be very thick but not dry; add a splash of water if necessary.

Stir in cilantro stems and remaining shallot. Season with @pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large, heavy-bottomed pan over medium-high heat. Add 1/4-cup scoops of batter and lightly press down to form small patties. Cook until golden brown and crisp, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a fork; stir in lime zest, @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and remaining cilantro leaves. Season with @salt.

Divide rice between plates and top with patties and salsa. Drizzle with crema and serve.